                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">1. mAh Capacity for OEM Buyers: Rated vs Usable & Cell Conversion Efficiency</h2>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">For OEM buyers specifying power bank cells, the gap between a cell's rated mAh and real-world usable capacity is the single most important technical specification to verify. Here's what mAh actually means and how to evaluate supplier claims.</p>

                    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
                        <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3">Rated vs Usable Capacity: The 60-70% Rule</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-4">Power bank capacity is measured at the internal battery voltage of <strong>3.7V</strong>, but USB output requires <strong>5V or higher</strong>. During this voltage step-up conversion, energy is lost as heat. The result: you only get about <strong>60-70% of the rated capacity</strong> as usable output.</p>
                        <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 rounded-xl p-5 border border-brandBlue/10 mb-4">
                            <p class="font-black text-brandBlue text-sm uppercase mb-2">The Conversion Formula</p>
                            <p class="text-slate-700 font-mono text-sm"><strong>Usable mAh = (Rated mAh × 3.7V × Efficiency) ÷ 5V</strong></p>
                            <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs mt-2">Example: 10,000mAh × 3.7V × 0.85 ÷ 5V = <strong>~6,290mAh usable</strong></p>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Premium power banks with GaN technology achieve 85-92% conversion efficiency. Budget models typically manage 60-75%. This is why two "10,000mAh" power banks can deliver noticeably different real-world performance. For a deeper technical breakdown, read our <a href="/blog/power-bank-specs-guide/" class="text-brandBlue hover:underline">Power Bank Specs Guide</a>.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
                        <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-4">Retail Packaging Reference: Estimated Full Charges by Device &amp; Capacity</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-xs mb-3">Use this reference table for retail packaging claims and Amazon product listings. All estimates based on conservative 65% conversion efficiency — <strong>OEM best practice: print the formula basis on packaging</strong> to reduce capacity-related returns.</p>
                        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                            <table class="w-full border border-slate-200 rounded-xl">
