                <section id="capacity-tiers" class="mb-16">
                    <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">2. OEM Capacity Tier Strategy: 5,000-27,000mAh with FOB Shenzhen Pricing</h2>
                    <div class="space-y-6">
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 text-xs font-black rounded-full">5,000mAh</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">~100-150g · FOB $3-5/unit at 1,000 pcs</span>
                            </div>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2"><strong>OEM Market Position:</strong> Ultra-portable entry tier — keychain and credit-card form factors. Lowest BOM cost, fastest production turnaround (15-20 days ODM). Best paired with semi-solid-state cells (as thin as 6.8mm) for premium differentiation.</p>
                            <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs">Target retail: $12-20. MOQ 500. Ideal first SKU for brands testing the market. Margin is thin on standard Li-polymer cells; semi-solid-state variant commands 2-3× retail premium. <a href="/blog/semi-solid-state-power-bank-oem/" class="text-brandBlue hover:underline">See semi-solid-state OEM guide →</a></p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border-2 border-brandOrange/30">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-brandOrange text-white text-xs font-black rounded-full">10,000mAh · HIGHEST VOLUME</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">~180-250g · FOB $4-7/unit at 1,000 pcs</span>
                            </div>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2"><strong>OEM Market Position:</strong> Captures <strong>47.89% of global market share</strong> — the volume driver for any power bank brand. GaN circuitry at this tier delivers 85-92% conversion efficiency vs 60-65% for budget designs, directly impacting retail reviews and return rates.</p>
                            <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs">Target retail: $20-40. MOQ 500. This is the tier where GaN vs non-GaN BOM decisions have the highest margin impact. Recommend 2-3 port variants (USB-C PD 20-30W + USB-A) to cover the broadest consumer base. WOWOHCOOL ships more 10,000mAh OEM units than all other tiers combined.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 text-xs font-black rounded-full">20,000mAh</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">~350-500g · FOB $8-14/unit at 1,000 pcs</span>
                            </div>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2"><strong>OEM Market Position:</strong> Travel and multi-device segment — 74Wh falls comfortably within IATA 100Wh carry-on limit (no airline approval needed). Higher BOM cost but higher retail margin ($40-60). Best paired with 65W+ PD output for tablet/ultrabook charging capability as a key differentiator.</p>
                            <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs">Target retail: $40-60. MOQ 500. Key certification requirements: UN38.3, CE, FCC, UL. 65W PD 3.0 output recommended as minimum to justify the 20,000mAh premium over 10,000mAh tier. Multi-port (2C1A) configuration is standard expectation at this tier.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 text-xs font-black rounded-full">27,000mAh+</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">~500-650g · FOB $14-22/unit at 1,000 pcs</span>
                            </div>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2"><strong>OEM Market Position:</strong> Laptop charging and professional segment — 99.9Wh sits exactly at the IATA 100Wh passenger aircraft limit. Requires 65-100W PD 3.1 EPR output to differentiate from 20,000mAh tier. Highest retail price point ($60-100+).</p>
                            <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs">Target retail: $60-100+. MOQ 500. Niche tier — only recommend for brands with established laptop accessory channels. EPR-rated cable must be included in-box (adds $2-4 to BOM). Airline compliance documentation (UN38.3 + Wh labeling) is mandatory for all distribution channels. Best combined with TFT display for real-time wattage monitoring as premium justification.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    </div>

